<SLUG fv=ttc-z> BC-BKN-<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CLIPPERS</ENAMEX>-LADN </SLUG>
<DATE> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">01-14</TIMEX> </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0594 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
BC-BKN-<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CLIPPERS</ENAMEX>-LADN
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CLIPPERS</ENAMEX>' STREAK ENDS WITH LOSS TO <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">ROCKETS</ENAMEX> 115-104
(For use by <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">NYTimes News Service</ENAMEX> clients)
By <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">SCOTT WOLF</ENAMEX>
c.<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1995</TIMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Los Angeles Daily News</ENAMEX>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">LOS ANGELES</ENAMEX>  The four-game winning streak that had served to
boost the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Los Angeles Clippers</ENAMEX>' morale, if not their place in the
standings, had its <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">midterm</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Saturday</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">night</TIMEX> with the arrival of
two-time world champion <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Houston</ENAMEX>.
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   It was not expansion <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Vancouver</ENAMEX>, beleaguered <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Phoenix</ENAMEX> or
struggling <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Minnesota</ENAMEX> that would test the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX>' best stretch
since <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the second week of the season</TIMEX>.
<p>
   Well, the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX> got the old ``A'' for effort, but the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Rockets</ENAMEX>
were not about to validate anything more, escaping with a 115-104
victory before 13,485 at the Sports Arena.
<p>
   The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX> (15-21) missed a chance to move out of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Pacific
Division</ENAMEX> cellar, but played one of their best halfs of the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">season</TIMEX>
during a <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">second-half</TIMEX> comeback that fell short.
<p>
   The main problem was a battle-tested <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Houston</ENAMEX> team that never
blinked even while nearly blowing a 22-point lead. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Hakeem Olajuwon</ENAMEX>
had 29 points and 17 rebounds, but converted only 8 of 24 shots.
<p>
   The real damage came from <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX> nemesis <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Clyde Drexler</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   The appearance of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX> was all <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Drexler</ENAMEX> needed to return
to form for the first time since missing eight games with a bruised
thigh. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Drexler</ENAMEX> made 5 of 6 of his 3-pointers and scored a game-high
32 points. He had made just 12 of 45 field goals entering the
contest, but usually plays his best against the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Drexler</ENAMEX> scored 27 against the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX> when the teams met in
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Houston</ENAMEX> in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">November</TIMEX>. He averaged 32 points against the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX>
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">last season</TIMEX>.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Drexler</ENAMEX>'s biggest 3-pointer came with <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">two minutes left</TIMEX>, and gave
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Houston</ENAMEX> a 99-93 advantage.
<p>
   The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX> made their comeback with the starters playing <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">all
12 minutes</TIMEX> in <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">the third quarter</TIMEX>.
<p>
   Their first substitution did not come until <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Pooh Richardson</ENAMEX>
suffered a strained right calf <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">early in the fourth quarter</TIMEX>.
<p>
   But the first string was earning its minutes, cutting the
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Rockets</ENAMEX>' lead to one-point (92-91) on <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Brian Williams</ENAMEX>' hook shot.
<p>
   But <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Houston</ENAMEX> never panicked and simply rebuilt the lead by
forcing the ball into <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Olajuwon</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Rockets</ENAMEX> (25-11), showing no signs of fatigue after losing to
the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Lakers</ENAMEX> on <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Friday</TIMEX>, were handling the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clippers</ENAMEX> in the <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">first half</TIMEX>
without a major contribution from <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Olajuwon</ENAMEX>. The big center made
only two of his first 11 shots in the <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">half</TIMEX>, but then keyed a 14-0
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Rockets</ENAMEX> run by scoring eight points.
<p>
   The spurt gave <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Houston</ENAMEX> a 54-32 lead and they eventually led by
20 points (58-38) at <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">halftime</TIMEX>.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Malik Sealy</ENAMEX> started the game despite suffering a hyperextended
knee against <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Minnesota</ENAMEX> on <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Thursday</TIMEX> while diving for a loose ball
with <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Doug West</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   He should be hurt more often. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sealy</ENAMEX> scored 27 points with eight
rebounds and four blocked shots before fouling out.
<p>
    &UR; Notes: &LR;  <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Rodney Rogers</ENAMEX> injured his right ankle on a drive in the
<TIMEX TYPE="TIME">first quarter</TIMEX> and did not return. It is the same ankle he hurt <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">last
month</TIMEX> that sidelined him for 15 games.... <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Stanley Roberts</ENAMEX>, still
out with a sprained ankle but expected back before <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the end of the
current homestand</TIMEX>, did not show up for a second straight game. He
has been bothered by the flu.... <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Pooh Richardson</ENAMEX> went 1 for 10 in
the <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">first half</TIMEX>. He did not play the entire <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">fourth quarter</TIMEX> in
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Thursday</TIMEX>'s victory over <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Minnesota</ENAMEX>. ``I can't get upset. I don't
make those decisions,'' <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Richardson</ENAMEX> said. ``I can't make those
decisions.'' <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Rockets</ENAMEX> forward <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Robert Horry</ENAMEX> did not dress, still
bothered by tendinitis in his right knee.
</TEXT>
