BC-<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">CLINTON</ENAMEX>-<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">CHINA</ENAMEX>-SATELLITES-BLOOM
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">CLINTON</ENAMEX> CLEARS <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">LOCKHEED</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">HUGHES</ENAMEX> TO SELL SATELLITES TO <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">CHINA</ENAMEX>
(For use by <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">New York Times News Service</ENAMEX> clients)
By <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Dina Temple-Raston</ENAMEX>
c.<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1996</TIMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bloomberg Business News</ENAMEX>
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Washington</ENAMEX>, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Feb. 6</TIMEX> (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bloomberg</ENAMEX>) -- President <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bill Clinton</ENAMEX> cleared
the way <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">today</TIMEX> for <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">General Motors Hughes Electronics Corp.</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Lockheed
Martin Corp.</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Loral Corp.</ENAMEX> to sell <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">hundreds of millions of
dollars</NUMEX> in satellites to <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   The president announced <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">this evening</TIMEX> that he has waived export
restrictions on <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">U.S.</ENAMEX> satellite technology bound for <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX> on three
Sino-<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">U.S.</ENAMEX> television, voice and data satellite projects.
Administration officials said that the projects had been awaiting a
green light from the president for some time.
<p>
   The first project, Cosat, will use two <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Lockheed Martin</ENAMEX>
satellites to provide voice, data and television to <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX>,
administration officials said. <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">China Orient Telecom Satellite Co.</ENAMEX>
is joining <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Lockheed</ENAMEX> in the project and will launch the satellite,
administration officials said.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">China Telecom Broadcast Satellite Corp.</ENAMEX> will be working with
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Hughes</ENAMEX>, a unit of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">General Motors Corp.</ENAMEX>, to launch a television and
data satellite for the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Chinasat</ENAMEX> project to provide television and
data to <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX>, the officials said.
<p>
   The third project would use <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Loral</ENAMEX> technology to beam voice and
data to the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Philippines</ENAMEX> and neighboring countries, the officials
said. Chinese rockets will launch the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Loral</ENAMEX> satellite and have
joined with the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Philippine Satellite Corp.</ENAMEX> in the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Mubuhay</ENAMEX> project.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Loral</ENAMEX> agreed <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">last month</TIMEX> to sell most of its operations to
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Lockheed Martin</ENAMEX>. None of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">U.S.</ENAMEX> companies had any immediate
comment on the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">White House</ENAMEX> announcement.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Clinton</ENAMEX> is waiving restrictions put in place by President <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">George
Bush</ENAMEX> in the wake of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1989</TIMEX> bloody suppression of pro-democracy
demonstrators by the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">People's Army</ENAMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Beijing</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bush</ENAMEX> put a freeze on
licenses for any technology that was on the munitions control list
-- including satellite technology.
<p>
   Both <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bush</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Clinton</ENAMEX> have issued waivers in the past. Under the
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">U.S.</ENAMEX> law, they can give the nod to projects that do not contribute
to the Chinese military and instead provide <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX> with more
information and communication technology.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Lockheed</ENAMEX> shares fell 3/4 <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">today</TIMEX> to close at 76. <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">GM</ENAMEX>'s Class H
shares fell 1/8 to 55 3/4. <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Loral</ENAMEX> shares fell 1/4 to 46 1/2.
</TEXT>
