<TEXT>
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Beijing</ENAMEX>, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 5</TIMEX> (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bloomberg</ENAMEX>) -- <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX> on <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Friday</TIMEX> will start a
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">week</TIMEX> of surface-to-surface missile tests in waters north and south
of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX>, the official <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Xinhua</ENAMEX> reported.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX>'s main stock index fell <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">0.6 percent</NUMEX> in the <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">first 5
minutes</TIMEX> of trading. ``Stocks will react poorly to the news,'' said
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Alex Lee</ENAMEX>, head of institutional sales at <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Yuanta Securities</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX>'s <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Broadcasting Corp.</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX> said the tests would be as
close as 12 miles from the northeastern part of the island.
<p>
   A <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Clinton</ENAMEX> Administration official downplayed the test, saying
they were expected.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Beijing</ENAMEX> has conducted the tests <TIMEX TYPE="DATE" MIN="last summer">since last summer</TIMEX> in a warning
to <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX> that it opposes the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX> President <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Lee Tung-hui</ENAMEX>'s
efforts to increase the island's international recognition.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Lee</ENAMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">last month</TIMEX> formally started his re-election campaign prior
to <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX>'s first direct presidential election on <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 23</TIMEX>.
<p>
   The increased tension caused <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX>'s stock market to plunge,
making it the world's worst performing market in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1996</TIMEX>.
<p>
   The <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Clinton</ENAMEX> Administration official, who spoke on the condition
of anonymity, said the tests announced <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">this morning</TIMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Beijing</ENAMEX> were
an expected continuation of previous tests that had been delayed by
bad weather.
<p>
   The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Xinhua</ENAMEX> report called for ships and aircraft to avoid the
areas in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">South China Sea</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">East China Sea</ENAMEX> where it will
conduct the test.
<p>
   ``For the sake of safety, the Chinese government requests the
governments of relevant countries and the authorities of relevant
regions to notify ships and aircraft of their countries and regions
not to enter the said sea areas and air spaces during <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">this
period</TIMEX>,'' <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Xinhua</ENAMEX> said.
