<PREAMBLE>
BC-<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">CHINA</ENAMEX>-<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">TAIWAN</ENAMEX>-MISSILES-BLOOM
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">CHINA</ENAMEX> FIRES 4TH TEST MISSILE NEAR <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">TAIWAN</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">TAIWAN</ENAMEX> MILITARY SAYS
(For use by <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">New York Times News Service</ENAMEX> clients)
By <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Russell Flannery</ENAMEX>
c.<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1996</TIMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bloomberg Business News</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taipei</ENAMEX>, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 13</TIMEX> (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bloomberg</ENAMEX>) -- <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">this morning</TIMEX> fired a test
missile near southern <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX>, the fourth in a series of launchings
that began on <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 8</TIMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX>'s <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Defense Ministry</ENAMEX> said in a
statement. The M-9 missile landed in a designated test area that
extends as close as 33 miles from the port city of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Kaohsiung</ENAMEX>, the
ministry said. <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX> on <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 8</TIMEX> fired three test missiles into the
same area near <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Kaohsiung</ENAMEX> and another zone about 22 miles northeast
of the northern port city of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Keelung</ENAMEX>. The missile tests are
scheduled to end on <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 15</TIMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX> has said. In separate
exercises, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">China</ENAMEX>'s army <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">yesterday</TIMEX> began <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">nine days</TIMEX> of
live-ammunition naval and air force drills in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan Strait</ENAMEX>.
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Beijing</ENAMEX> admits the tests are intended to intimidate <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Taiwan</ENAMEX> voters
ahead of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 23</TIMEX> elections. <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">U.S.</ENAMEX> Secretary of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">State</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Warren
Christopher</ENAMEX> has called the tests ``unnecessary and provocative,''
and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Washington</ENAMEX> has dispatched warships to the area.
</PREAMBLE>
