BC-<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">BAUER</ENAMEX>-ACCOUNT-SFCHRON
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Eddie Bauer</ENAMEX> Pulls Account From <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Riney</ENAMEX>
By <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">JULIA ANGWIN</ENAMEX>
c.<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1996</TIMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">San Francisco Chronicle</ENAMEX>
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Seattle</ENAMEX>-based retailer <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Eddie Bauer Inc.</ENAMEX> has pulled its <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$4
million</NUMEX> advertising account from the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">San Francisco</ENAMEX> ad firm, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Hal
Riney &AMP; Partners</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   The move comes after three top <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Riney</ENAMEX> executives who worked on
the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Eddie Bauer</ENAMEX> business left to form their own agency, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Black
Rocket</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   While at <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Riney</ENAMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">last year</TIMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Black Rocket</ENAMEX> founders <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">John Yost</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Steve
Stone</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mark Barden</ENAMEX> created the first national advertising
campaign for the apparel company.
<p>
   The print ads, which were launched in magazines around the
country <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">this month</TIMEX>, show outdoor scenes of people roasting
marshmallows and contain directions for making s'mores. The tag
line reads, ``Never confuse having a career with having a life.''
<p>
   The ads, which may expand into television, were designed to make
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Eddie Bauer</ENAMEX> into a brand name.
<p>
   The outdoor-oriented sportswear and footwear retailer is a
subsidiary of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Spiegel Inc.</ENAMEX>, and operates 294 retail stores and a
mail order catalog.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Eddie Bauer</ENAMEX> spokeswoman <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sheryl Engstrom</ENAMEX> confirmed that the
company has parted ways with <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Riney</ENAMEX>, but declined to confirm
industry speculation that the ad business will move to <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Black
Rocket</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Hal Riney</ENAMEX> managing director <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">David Verklin</ENAMEX> said the split was
amicable, since it was never intended to be an ongoing
relationship.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Engstrom</ENAMEX> said the retailer has awarded the media buying portion
of the account to <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Creative Media</ENAMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">San Francisco</ENAMEX> and is shopping
for an agency to handle the creative portion.
<p>
   ``I think they're going to use <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Black Rocket</ENAMEX> for a TV campaign,''
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Verklin</ENAMEX> said.
<p>
   If <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Black Rocket</ENAMEX> wins that account, it would be the fledgling
agency's third since it was formed in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">February</TIMEX>.
<p>
   The firm is also promoting <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Yahoo!</ENAMEX>, an Internet search company,
and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Tri Valley Growers</ENAMEX>, a <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Bay Area</ENAMEX> agricultural cooperative.
</TEXT>
