<PREAMBLE>
BC-BBN-DODGERNOTES-LADN
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">BUTLER</ENAMEX> HAS TONSILS REMOVED
(For use by <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">NYTimes News Service</ENAMEX> clients)
By <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">TIM BROWN</ENAMEX>
c.<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1996</TIMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Los Angeles Daily News</ENAMEX>
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">PITTSBURGH</ENAMEX>  &MD;  <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Los Angeles Dodgers</ENAMEX> center fielder <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Brett Butler</ENAMEX> had
successful surgery <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Friday</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">morning</TIMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Atlanta</ENAMEX> to have his tonsils
removed.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Butler</ENAMEX> was at home in nearby <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Duluth</ENAMEX> by <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Friday</TIMEX> <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">afternoon</TIMEX> and
planned to watch the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Dodgers</ENAMEX> play the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Pittsburgh Pirates</ENAMEX> via
satellite, his wife, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Eveline</ENAMEX>, said.
<p>
   ``I told him I'd let him try, as long as he doesn't get antsy,
he can watch,'' she said. ``If he doesn't behave I'll take it away
an inning at a time.''
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Butler</ENAMEX>, who is on the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">15-day</TIMEX> disabled list and could miss up to
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">three weeks</TIMEX>, was taking fluids immediately after the procedure and
was able to speak. He will not be allowed any activity for <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the next
10 to 14 days</TIMEX>, while the wound heals. At <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">that time</TIMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Butler</ENAMEX> will
begin light stretching.
<p>
   ``The biggest concern was that it would start bleeding,''
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Eveline Butler</ENAMEX> said.
<p>
   Tonsillectomy patients often lose 10 or more pounds during
recovery, and therefore <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Butler</ENAMEX> will begin <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">today</TIMEX> with a diet of
high-calorie, high-protein drinks.
<p>
   As for the talkative <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Butler</ENAMEX>'s fear that he would not be able to
speak for days, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Eveline</ENAMEX> said, ``<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Brett</ENAMEX> was up and out of it and
talking in <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">an hour</TIMEX>. I said, `Oh darn.' ''
<p>
    &UR; Good news, bad news:  &LR; Shortly after being told he would join
the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Dodgers</ENAMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Pittsburgh</ENAMEX> as the roster replacement for <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Butler</ENAMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mike Busch</ENAMEX> learned that his <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">16-month</TIMEX>-old daughter, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Shunyl</ENAMEX>,
fractured her pelvis and would be in a body cast for <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">six weeks</TIMEX>.
<p>
   ``The doctor told me she's going to be fine,'' <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Busch</ENAMEX> said.
``That's all you can do.
<p>
   ``I can't turn this opportunity down.''
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Busch</ENAMEX>, a right-handed bat off the bench the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Dodgers</ENAMEX> have lacked,
hit .320 with five homers and 17 RBI at Triple-A <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Albuquerque</ENAMEX>,
despite a foot injury.
<p>
   ``I was confident out of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">spring</TIMEX> training and just took that into
the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">season</TIMEX>,'' <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Busch</ENAMEX> said. ``I knew I had the ability to be up here.
I had the confidence.
<p>
   ``The uncertainty wasn't there. I knew what was up here.''
<p>
    &UR; Notes:  &LR; Shortstop <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Greg Gagne</ENAMEX> returned to the lineup after
resting his strained hamstring for five games. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gagne</ENAMEX> said the
hamstring was better, though he feared six consecutive games on
artificial turf, in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Pittsburgh</ENAMEX> and in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Cincinnati</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">St. Louis</ENAMEX> has
replaced its turf with grass.... Minor-league infielder <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Garey
Ingram</ENAMEX> had surgery <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Friday</TIMEX> to repair his right rotator cuff....
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Albuquerque</ENAMEX> outfielder <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Karim Garcia</ENAMEX> had his left elbow examined by
Dr. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Frank Jobe</ENAMEX>, who found a strain.
</TEXT>
