BC-OLY-HELICOPTERS-COX
SUPER SYSTEM WILL GUIDE HELICOPTER TRAFFIC DURING GAMES
By <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">DAVID GOLDBERG</ENAMEX>
c. <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1996</TIMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Cox News Service</ENAMEX>
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">ATLANTA</ENAMEX>  &MD;  With roads in possible gridlock during the Olympics,
helicopters could be the saving grace for people who need immediate
medical attention or a critical business delivery.
<p>
   But how to prevent sky-lock, given the swarm of helicopters
expected, possibly several times the 74 copters normally stationed
in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Atlanta</ENAMEX>?
<p>
   A federal demonstration project could help transportation
officials get a handle on at least some of them by using global
positioning satellite navigation and something like airborne e-mail
to guide emergency and special cargo copters.
<p>
   The <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$10 million</NUMEX> project unveiled <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Monday</TIMEX> and paid for by the
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Federal Aviation Administration</ENAMEX> (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">FAA</ENAMEX>), <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">NASA</ENAMEX> and private companies
will keep track of 50 choppers. About half of them will be under
the control of emergency officials. Others agencies and businesses
with time-sensitive deliveries, such as <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Federal Express</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">The
Atlanta Journal- Constitution</ENAMEX>, also will participate.
<p>
   ``This is an important experiment,'' said <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">FAA</ENAMEX> administrator
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">David Hinson</ENAMEX>. The project marks the first attempt to coordinate
helicopter movements in the crowded skies above a dense urban area,
he said.
<p>
   At monitoring stations at <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Dobbins Air Force Base</ENAMEX> and the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Georgia
Emergency Management Association</ENAMEX> downtown, a computer will show a
map of metro <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Atlanta</ENAMEX> and its interstate highway system. Cockpit
displays in the helicopter will show pilots what the weather and
other air traffic looks like. .
</TEXT>
