<SLUG fv=tia-z> BC-<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX>-CABLE-TV-UPDATE1- </SLUG>
<DATE> <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">08-20</TIMEX> </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0454 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
BC-<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX>-CABLE-TV-UPDATE1-BLOOM
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">WESTINGHOUSE</ENAMEX>'S <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> TO LAUNCH NEW CABLE TV CHANNEL (UPDATE1)
(For use by <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">New York Times News Service</ENAMEX> clients)
By <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Karen Fessler</ENAMEX>
c.<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1996</TIMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bloomberg Business News</ENAMEX>
   (Adds analyst comment in third and seventh paragraphs,
background on retransmission deadline in fifth and sixth
paragraphs.)
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">New York</ENAMEX>, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Aug. 20</TIMEX> (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Bloomberg</ENAMEX>) -- <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Westinghouse Electric Corp.</ENAMEX>'s
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> said it plans to launch a new cable television channel focusing
on people and using programming from its news, entertainment and
sports divisions.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> also formed an alliance with <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Discover Communications Inc.</ENAMEX> --
parent of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Discovery Channel</ENAMEX> -- to create programming for the
Eye on the People channel, a name that will capitalize on the
network's eye-shaped symbol.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Westinghouse</ENAMEX> Chairman <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Michael ``Jordan</ENAMEX> realizes he's behind in
the cable race and they have to get something going as soon as
possible,'' said analyst <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Art Rockwell</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Yaeger Capital Markets</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   The channel, to be launched <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">March 31</TIMEX>, is the latest push by
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Weztinghouse</ENAMEX> to expand into cable television. The company owns a
stake in <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Gaylord Entertainment Co.</ENAMEX>, parent of the Country Music
cable channel, and <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">last month</TIMEX> bought <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">TeleNoticias</ENAMEX>, a
Spanish-language channel for Latin American cable and satellite
viewers.
<p>
   The new cable channel gives <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> leverage with local cable
operators. Without the cable channel, operators had the right under
federal regulations to carry the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> network without compensating
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX>.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> declined to say whether any cable companies have agreed to
carry the channel, which will consist of ``original reality-based
programming will focus on people, contemporary and historical, in
and out of the headlines,'' <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> said.
<p>
   Having a cable channel ``gives them more bargaining power with
the cable operators,'' <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Rockwell</ENAMEX> said.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX>, the only network not to have its own cable channel,
announced the channel <TIMEX TYPE="DATE" MIN="six weeks">six weeks before an <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Oct. 1</TIMEX> deadline</TIMEX> set by
federal regulations that governs whether cable operators can be
compensated for carrying just the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> network.
<p>
   The three other major networks already have cable channels. <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">News
Corp.</ENAMEX>'s <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Fox</ENAMEX> has <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">fX</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Walt Disney Co.</ENAMEX>'s <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">ABC</ENAMEX> has <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">ESPN2</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">General
Electric Co.</ENAMEX>'s <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">NBC</ENAMEX> has <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">MSNBC</ENAMEX>, formerly <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">America's Talking</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX> said
it will use programming and production resources from its <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS News</ENAMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS Sports</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS Entertainment</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Eyemark Entertainment</ENAMEX> and the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">CBS</ENAMEX>
and <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Group W</ENAMEX> archives.
<p>
   <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Westinghouse</ENAMEX>'s <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Group W Network Services</ENAMEX> will handle production
and satellite distribution of the channel.
<p>
   ``This is an important strategic step for <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Westinghouse/CBS</ENAMEX> that
establishes a new position in the multichannel universe,'' said
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Michael Jordan</ENAMEX>, chairman and chief executive of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Westinghouse</ENAMEX>.
